law.text:
An optometrist practicing in the State may not:
Use surgical lasers;
Perform any surgery, including cataract surgery or cryosurgery;
Perform a radial keratotomy;
Give an injection, except that an optometrist may give an injection of epinephrine in the appropriate dose for the treatment of acute anaphylaxis or emergency resuscitation; or
Except as provided under this title, dispense a therapeutic pharmaceutical agent to any person.
